# Implementation Plan: Light Mode as Default UI Overhaul

The goal is to transition the entire application UI from a dark-themed default to a premium, high-contrast light-themed default, while maintaining dark mode as an optional preference.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change will fundamentally alter the visual identity of the app. I am opting for a "Zinc" based palette (Off-white background, deep charcoal text) to ensure a premium look that isn't eye-straining.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Theme System

#### [MODIFY] [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/globals.css)
- Define a comprehensive set of CSS variables in `:root` for light mode.
- Move current dark mode colors into a `.dark` class or `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` block.
- Update `@theme` block to map these variables to Tailwind utilities.

### Core Layout & Home

#### [MODIFY] [layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/layout.tsx)
- Ensure the `html` or `body` element doesn't have hardcoded `dark` classes.
- Add support for a theme toggle (optional, but good for UX).

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/page.tsx)
- Replace hardcoded `bg-black`, `bg-zinc-950`, `text-white`, etc. with semantic theme-aware classes.

---

### UI Components

#### [MODIFY] `src/components/ui/*.tsx`
- Systematically update [Card](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#514-606), `Badge`, [Button](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#76-103), `Popover`, etc. to use semantic classes (e.g., `bg-card`, `text-card-foreground`, `border-border`).

---

### Feature Components

#### [MODIFY] [DailyMeetingView.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx)
- This is a large file with many hardcoded colors (especially in [AllPersonsView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#75-229) and [SquadsView](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/DailyMeetingView.tsx#243-835)). I will replace these with theme-aware utilities.
- Adjust status-specific colors (Doing, Blocking, Blocked) to look good on light backgrounds.

#### [MODIFY] Other Dashboard Views
- `NextSprintPlanningView.tsx`
- `DailyRecapView.tsx`
- `PersonnelOverview.tsx`
- `TaskOverview.tsx`
- `SprintStartManager.tsx`

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- No existing UI tests found. I will rely on manual visual verification using the browser.

### Manual Verification
- **Visual Audit**: Navigate through all tabs (Daily Meeting, Next Sprint Planning, etc.) in Light Mode.
- **Contrast Check**: Ensure all text is readable and status indicators (badges, dots) have sufficient contrast.
- **Dark Mode Check**: Manually toggle the system theme to ensure the application still looks good in Dark Mode (if supported via media query).
- **Interactive Elements**: Verify hover states and active states for buttons and tabs.
- **Scrollbars**: Ensure custom scrollbars look good on light backgrounds.
